Defendant Christopher Charles High in court with attorney Daniel C. Nedset.  Dennis Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
As to Count  1 :
Parties have reached a resolution in this matter.
Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by defense counsel and defendant.
As to Count 1:
Defendant changes his/her plea to GUILTY. Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum previously efiled.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction. Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he/she may never possess a firearm, ammunition or body armor. Court advised defendant that his/her voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his/her civil rights are restored.
*
Sentencing hearing proceeded with statements from state, defense and defendant. State has complied with victim notification. 
The Court ordered the Defendant to:
- Serve 6 months days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence.  Huber privileges for work with credit for 5 days time served.
Court further ordered:
- Fine of $1000.00 plus costs, fees and assessments
- 2 years drivers license revocation.
- 1 year months ignition interlock.
- AODA assessment.

Court set restitution at zero.
Court ordered defendant provide a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharges.

All costs, surcharges and assessment  (including the DNA surcharges) to be paid by 7/13/2022,  to convert to a civil judgment.  Any cash bail on deposit to apply.
